com.iver.cit.gvsig.fmap.layers
Class DefaultDimension

java.lang.Object
  com.iver.cit.gvsig.fmap.layers.DefaultDimension
All Implemented Interfaces:
IFMapWMSDimension
public class DefaultDimension
extends java.lang.Object
implements IFMapWMSDimension

This class instances a regular WMS dimension. It handles single, multiple and interval values and uses them as they were a point, a list or a regularly split line, respectivelly.

As far as it implements IFMapWMSDimension it uses the same interface and documentation.

Author:
jaume dominguez faus (jaume.dominguez@iver.es)

isValidValue

public boolean isValidValue(java.lang.String value)
Description copied from interface: IFMapWMSDimension
Checks if the value represented as string is a valid value by checking if the dimensions supports it. It should be true if one of the following is true:

  1. The dimension supports nearest values and the value is greather or equal than the low limit and less or equal than the high limit.
  2. The value matches in one of the points defined by the low and high limits, and the resolution value.
